# No inset accent bars

Do not use left-edge accent bars for selection/diff/highlight states.

Forbidden patterns:
- `box-shadow: inset Npx 0 0 <color>` (or any inset shadow used as a left rail)
- Thick left borders used as a “selected row” indicator
- Chamfered / blocky corner treatments on highlight rails

Prefer instead:
- Flat background fills only (e.g. soft green/red wash on the whole row/cell/line)
- Optional subtle `mark` / text highlight without edge rails

This applies especially to markdown diff preview, tables, lists, and code line highlights.
